The paper deals with shape formation by mobile entities, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of programmable matter and limited computational power of the entities also suggests a connection to distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of an adversarial scheduler, which is a common topic in control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of the algorithm used, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
